@host = http://localhost:5206

### 📋 List all available endpoints
GET {{host}}/
Accept: application/json

### ❌ Scenario 1: DI + duplicate detection — "admin" username and email taken
POST {{host}}/api/register/duplicate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123"
}

### ❌ Scenario 2: Invalid email format — async two-phase validation skips UniqueEmail
POST {{host}}/api/register/bad-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123"
}

### ❌ Scenario 3: Invalid money transfer — same account + exceeds balance
POST {{host}}/api/transfer/invalid
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "checking",
  "toAccount": "checking",
  "amount": 1000.00
}

### ❌ Scenario 4: Infrastructure error — "error-trigger" causes DB failure
POST {{host}}/api/register/error
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "error-trigger",
  "email": "new@example.com",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123"
}

### ⚠️ Scenario 5: CancellationToken propagation — request abort/timeout can cancel validation
POST {{host}}/api/register/cancellation
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newuser",
  "email": "new@example.com",
  "password": "SecureP@ss123"
}
